<h1>Cornered Image Box</h1>
<p>A corner image placed in each corner of a box, all done in CSS only.</p>

<h2>Usage</h2>
<p>Usage is pretty straightforward:</p>
<ul>
<li>Add the rules from the style.css to your own stylesheet.</li>
<li>Add the image to your image folder and make the path to this image in your style sheet point to it.</li>
<li>Create a div with the class"boxHolder" and puut your content in it.</li>
<li>After that div, create 4 empty divs.  Add the classes "topLeft", "topRight", "bottomLeft" and "bottomRight" respectively to each one (one per div, see the demo).  </li>
<li>Enjoy!</li>
</ul>

</body>
</html>
